      <section id="main_content" class="inner">
        <h1>
<a name="josef-hoffmann" class="anchor" href="#josef-hoffmann"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>TEAPOT</h1>
<font size="4">
<div>
<p><img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/js-partial-teapot-form.png?raw=true" alt="carafe-form-js" style="width:200px; heigth:200px;" align="right"></p>
Since the very geometric shape of the teapot I decided to build a field for each element and rotate around the z axis.
<p><img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/js-teapot-form.png?raw=true" alt="teapot-form-js" style="width:300px; heigth:30px;" align="left">
I have therefore defined the form of a single sector of the teapot, through Hermite and Bezier curves and Coons patches, I then replicated the shape and colored it of two different colors: black and white.
Then this figure is obtained by rotating the volume of the teapot.</p>
<pre>
var Su0 = CUBIC_HERMITE(S0)([[COS(PI/6),SIN(PI/12),0],[COS(PI/6),-SIN(PI/12),0],[TAN(PI/6),0,0],[0,TAN(PI/6),0]]);
var Su1 = CUBIC_HERMITE(S0)([[0.2+COS(PI/6),SIN(PI/12),1.9],[0.2+COS(PI/6),(-SIN(PI/12)),1.9],[TAN(PI/6),0,0],[0,TAN(PI/6),0]]);
var Sv0 = BEZIER(S1)([[COS(PI/6),SIN(PI/12),0],[COS(PI/6)+0.4,SIN(PI/12)+0.2,0.6],[COS(PI/6)+0.4,SIN(PI/12)+0.2,1.3],[COS(PI/6),SIN(PI/12),1.9]]);
var Sv1 = BEZIER(S1)([[COS(PI/6),-SIN(PI/12),0],[COS(PI/6)+0.4,-SIN(PI/12)-0.2,0.6],[COS(PI/6)+0.4,-SIN(PI/12)-0.2,1.3],[COS(PI/6),-SIN(PI/12),1.9]]);
var tp1 = MAP(COONS_PATCH([Su0,Su1,Sv0,Sv1]))(dom2D);
</pre>
<p>
I have added the fund by rotating a circular arc (created using the function arc).
I then generated through the lid of the sphere function and a bounded domain to PI/3 in height and PI/6 in width. Then I turned the sector achieved.</p>
<p><img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/js-teapot-cup.png?raw=true" alt="teapot cover" style="width:300px; heigth:30px;" align="center"></p>
Finally I created the knob, the spouth and the handle through a patch of coons.
<p><img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/js-teapot-spout.png?raw=true" alt="spouth-teapot-js" style="width:320px; heigth:320px;" align="left">
<p><img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/js-teapot-handle.png?raw=true" alt="handle-teapot-js" style="width:280px; heigth:280px;" align="left"></p>
</br>
<p>
This is the result obtained in python and javascript</p>

<p><img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/teapot-js.png?raw=true" alt="sugar-bowl-js" style="width:300px; heigth:30px;">
<img src="https://github.com/stederob/Final-Project/blob/gh-pages/images/melon%20service/py-teapot.png?raw=true" style="width:300px; heigth:30px;">
</div>
